<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-251] HSM event name typos in Chapter 22 - Hierarchical Storage Management</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-251</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are typos in Chapter 22 of the Lustre Manual, which describes Hierarchical Storage Management.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In section 22.7 on changelogs, all of the HSM events are listed with the same name, HE_STATE.  This should match the enum definition in the code (without the spares, of course):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;enum&lt;/span&gt; hsm_event {                  
        HE_ARCHIVE      = 0,
        HE_RESTORE      = 1,
        HE_CANCEL       = 2,
        HE_RELEASE      = 3,
        HE_REMOVE       = 4,
        HE_STATE        = 5,
        HE_SPARE1       = 6,
        HE_SPARE2       = 7,
};      
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
